definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To notch , as a sword or knife.
( transitive ) To make an opening in; to breach .
( transitive ) To check the size of a gap.
examples: I gapped all the spark plugs in my car, but then realized I had used the wrong manual and had made them too small.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , intransitive , slang , especially video games , motor racing ) To surpass (someone or something) by a considerable margin .
( New Zealand , slang ) To leave suddenly.
( intransitive ) To fall or spill open so as to leave a gap.
